channel.title: No-Name Project
channel.description:
Hello all,
It's been a very long time since I have actually done any projects/programming more than a year at least so this will be a little...slow at first. I am not honestly sure what I am aiming for. I have played several rsps in the recent week mostly out of depression and they all seem to lack one thing or another. Below are my aims somewhat:
[u][b]Goals/Aims: [/b][/u]
-Content filled -As bug free as I can make it I don't claim to be "pro" but I am not scared of asking for help either! -At the current time it will not to be hosted however if there is enough desire later much later in the future...we shall see -I want this to be a learning experience. When I stopped programming I was at the learning curve where everything started to make more and more sense and I fear what stopping at that gap may have or not have done.
[b][u]Skills:[/u][/b]
As most of you know I am mostly a skiller on RuneScape/private servers purely because just that, I like to skill. I most likely will NOT be focusing on combat. If I ever decide to actually host I will probably have to get somebody to assist me in rewriting combat entirely.
The skills on the server will be as near to 100% as I can make them and as bug free as I can make them. I may even host a day of testing for specific skills only when the time comes. Please keep in mind that all of this is in future stages as I will first have to clear out my old source and rewrite well... a crap load of stuff xD...
[b][u]Skill that's are in need/will be done[/u][/b]
*Please note the sprites I downloaded and all are a higher revision and was intentional however I do plan to downgrade the skill interface cause this most likely won't have dungeonering etc in it. (just the basic stuff from 377 or so)
Legend: Not started/Currently being worked on/Completed
-Agility (ALL COURSES ON 474!) -RuneCrafting -Fletching/Woodcutting/firemaking ( I normally design these all at the same time on purpose as I train them at the same time ) -Mining / Smithing ( ^ ) -Fishing/Cooking ( ^ ) -Farming/herblore ( ^ ) -Thieving -Crafting ( I may or may not do all content for this skill the unreleased version of myth-scape had like 85% of all crafting already in it and I really don't feel like rewriting it all again as I don't have my old files so we shall see... )
[b][u]Update Log: [/u][/b]
[u]Feb 1, 2014[/u] -Removed all skills except crafting at the moment(not that this source had many anyway...) --Repackaged (pretty much to look like PI packaging and that's only because I actually liked the way it was packaged overall besides a couple of minor path differences ) [u]Feb 2, 2014[/u] -Added basic clipping system (I will consult with a couple of friends on how this system can be improved at a future date) [s]-Started work on agility (Ape atoll mostly :)...hopefully I didn't chew off more than I can chew I can already tell I will have some difficulty with this but I am up for the challenge! ) [/s] UPDATED see below -Fixed a couple of nullpointers I was getting in logout/while banking as well -Totally removed starter cause I don't believe in having a bunch of crap and probably won't even have one in the first place.... -found out how to use the camera packet ( thank you arham <3 ) -completed adding basic ape atoll data, course is fully functional mostly bug fixes now -started working on werewolf course...will probably finish around Tuesday I don't have all the data I need so will have to do some research ;) (where is nolan when I need him :( ) -made a strong attempt at cleaning out some of client class...yeah.... still a long way to go ... [u]2/5/14[/u] -Added grahams event system ( still has a few issues I am working out ) I at least attempted my own system and it just yeah... so yeah... I will attempt it again later however I do not feel at this time I can honestly develop one as it should be. -Werewolf course progress ( I still need some animations if anybody wishes to help...) was unable to get a better picture due to the event system constantly throwing errors whenever an event is done ( I actually got nulled or something right after I took picture...) -Started working on my firemaking skill as well but not ready to post picture of it. [u]2/7/13[/u] Nothing too major was done today but here you go -completed firemaking to the best of my abilities this includes --log fire that moves with proper clipping -has proper gfx/timer -hd client support for the firemaking ( in other words it isn't like the original crappy firemaking gfx where it stays still :p ) -can't light in bank/duel arena type of stuff and other minigames not that I have any at the moment! -can't light fires on top of each -added the multi color fire thingies I forget what they are called ( again lol...firestarters~^ ) In other news... -started woodcutting base currently supports chopping trees but nothing else still need to make stumps, timers, proper ax for each level etc etc
[b][u]Pictures[/u][/b]
[IMG]http://i.imgur.com/xLQDKfm.png?1[/img]
*Picture somewhat outdated but will do the job* [IMG]http://i.imgur.com/aP0Ejac.png?1[/img]
[b][u]Credits[/u][/b]
[IMG]http://i.imgur.com/rFrbYS4.png?1[/img]
-Myself for the content that will be added -Nolan an ex staff member of mine from FJ who has given me oodles and oodles of id's/data in the past which will assist me with the project -Paladino (as I assume it's his clipping system that he wrote from the java docs for stuff like that -David a good friend of mine who actually encouraged I try to get back into the hang of things and somebody who is always there when I need to ramble on :) -Amy same thing about the rambling part can't forget her :P <3 you babygirl -Whoever the source/client owner of this source this is originally an allstar of some kind but I can't state for sure exactly who the owner is. -arham 4 ( for camera stuffs from froyoscape )

item.title: No-Name Project
item.dc:creator: @Loveandpower Loveandpower
item.description:
@Loveandpower wrote:

[quote=“Clawz fury, post:14, topic:539582”]don’t use Graham’s task scheduler, just make your own so you can make it as flexible as you want and completely adaptable to your server

also iirc graham’s task scheduler is completely single threaded which means that it can’t handle more than one task simultaneously which can cause something like

-submit task-
Thread-1: carried out task
-submit task-
Thread-1: carried out task
-submit big task-
Thread-1: carrying out task
-submit task-

if that thread is still carrying out the task, then the last task we submitted will have to wait until the thread is done because we only have one thread handling tasks

this causes a delay depending on the size of the task that had to be carried out (usually small) which means: inaccurate timing

you COULD just use graham’s task scheduler and make it run on a scheduled thread pool instead (you would only have to change one line)

but don’t take anything I say too seriously because I’m not an expert on concurrency and that whole explanation could be wrong

@project: are you planning to host this?[/quote]thanks for the insight I discussed some stuff with ryley yesterday as well ( I need to check skype actually )

Had a rough day at work so no updates tonight

and to answer your question…I am still undecided but at this time probably not. This is really more for enjoyment/my own pickyness Anybody who has had me beta test knows how…cruel I can be .

item.title: No-Name Project
item.dc:creator: @Loveandpower Loveandpower
item.description:
@Loveandpower wrote:

Hello all,

It’s been a very long time since I have actually done any projects/programming more than a year at least so this will be a little…slow at first. I am not honestly sure what I am aiming for. I have played several rsps in the recent week mostly out of depression and they all seem to lack one thing or another. Below are my aims somewhat:

Goals/Aims:

-Content filled
-As bug free as I can make it I don’t claim to be “pro” but I am not scared of asking for help either!
-At the current time it will not to be hosted however if there is enough desire later much later in the future…we shall see
-I want this to be a learning experience. When I stopped programming I was at the learning curve where everything started to make more and more sense and I fear what stopping at that gap may have or not have done.

Skills:

As most of you know I am mostly a skiller on RuneScape/private servers purely because just that, I like to skill. I most likely will NOT be focusing on combat. If I ever decide to actually host I will probably have to get somebody to assist me in rewriting combat entirely.

The skills on the server will be as near to 100% as I can make them and as bug free as I can make them. I may even host a day of testing for specific skills only when the time comes. Please keep in mind that all of this is in future stages as I will first have to clear out my old source and rewrite well… a crap load of stuff xD…

Skill that’s are in need/will be done

*Please note the sprites I downloaded and all are a higher revision and was intentional however I do plan to downgrade the skill interface cause this most likely won’t have dungeonering etc in it. (just the basic stuff from 377 or so)

Legend: Not started/Currently being worked on/Completed

-Agility (ALL COURSES ON 474!)
-RuneCrafting
-Fletching/Woodcutting/firemaking ( I normally design these all at the same time on purpose as I train them at the same time )
-Mining / Smithing ( ^ )
-Fishing/Cooking ( ^ )
-Farming/herblore ( ^ )
-Thieving
-Crafting ( I may or may not do all content for this skill the unreleased version of myth-scape had like 85% of all crafting already in it and I really don’t feel like rewriting it all again as I don’t have my old files so we shall see… )

Update Log:

Feb 1, 2014
-Removed all skills except crafting at the moment(not that this source had many anyway…)
–Repackaged (pretty much to look like PI packaging and that’s only because I actually liked the way it was packaged overall besides a couple of minor path differences )
Feb 2, 2014
-Added basic clipping system (I will consult with a couple of friends on how this system can be improved at a future date)
-Started work on agility (Ape atoll mostly :)…hopefully I didn’t chew off more than I can chew I can already tell I will have some difficulty with this but I am up for the challenge! ) UPDATED see below
-Fixed a couple of nullpointers I was getting in logout/while banking as well
-Totally removed starter cause I don’t believe in having a bunch of crap and probably won’t even have one in the first place…
-found out how to use the camera packet ( thank you arham <3 )
-completed adding basic ape atoll data, course is fully functional mostly bug fixes now
-started working on werewolf course…will probably finish around Tuesday I don’t have all the data I need so will have to do some research (where is nolan when I need him )
-made a strong attempt at cleaning out some of client class…yeah… still a long way to go …
2/5/14
-Added grahams event system ( still has a few issues I am working out ) I at least attempted my own system and it just yeah… so yeah… I will attempt it again later however I do not feel at this time I can honestly develop one as it should be.
-Werewolf course progress ( I still need some animations if anybody wishes to help…) was unable to get a better picture due to the event system constantly throwing errors whenever an event is done ( I actually got nulled or something right after I took picture…)
-Started working on my firemaking skill as well but not ready to post picture of it.
2/7/13
Nothing too major was done today but here you go
-completed firemaking to the best of my abilities this includes
